cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and statistical analysis of text data, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper specifically focuses on clustering and segmentation of multilingual texts, which suggests a stronger emphasis on computational linguistics and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.DL.
